BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sight-geist-rubin-foundation-2026-27@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260620T074418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260705
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260706
SUMMARY:Deadline: Sight/Geist Season 7: Film & Performance Open Call for Em
 erging NYC Artists
DESCRIPTION:Seventh season of Sight/Geist\, a series from the Shelley & Don
 ald Rubin Foundation supporting emerging NYC-based film and performance ar
 tists. The Foundation provides curatorial\, administrative and promotional
  support\, plus documentation for performances and discussions\; selected 
 artists also engage in a Q&A on their broader practice. TWO CATEGORIES: (1
 ) single-channel screening - experimental/non-commercial cinema\, video ar
 t or performance documentation as a single-channel non-looped projection w
 ith 2.1 PA\; H.264 or ProRes\; under 80 minutes (priority to <20 min)\; (2
 ) performance and expanded forms - 20-50 minutes\; may foreground duration
 \, movement\, audiovisual media\, voice\, site specificity\, audience part
 icipation\; conceptual and political proposals encouraged. ELIGIBILITY: pr
 imary applicant must be at least 18 and maintain their primary residence i
 n New York City (or spend most of their artistic\, professional and social
  life in NYC)\; self-identify as an 'emerging' artist (early-career\, self
 -trained\, newly graduated\, or currently enrolled in undergraduate/gradua
 te programs)\; one submission per artist/duo/collective. Submissions open 
 1 June through 11 pm ET\, 5 July 2026\; applicants notified by late August
  2026. Contact: info@the8thfloor.org.\n\nOrganisation: Shelley & Donald Ru
 bin Foundation (The 8th Floor)\nLocation: The 8th Floor\, near Union Squar
 e\, New York City\, United States\nAward: Fixed artist fees: $300 for a gr
 oup screening\; $500 for a solo screening\; $750 for a solo performance\, 
 with an additional $250 for reimbursable production costs (collaborators\,
  materials\, transportation\, rehearsal\, specific AV/lighting beyond the 
 gallery inventory). For duos and collectives the fees are shared. The prim
 ary applicant must be able to submit an invoice and US tax form to receive
  payment. No application fee.\nDuration: 2026/27 programming season at The
  8th Floor\n\nMore: https://www.sdrubin.org/artists
URL:https://www.sdrubin.org/artists
LOCATION:The 8th Floor\, near Union Square\, New York City\, United States
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:axs-film-fund-open-call-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260620T074418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: AXS Film Fund Open Call 2026
DESCRIPTION:Grants from the AXS Film Fund supporting documentary and nonfic
 tion new media creators\, particularly those who identify as living with a
  disability and especially from underserved communities\, though applicati
 ons are welcome from all creators regardless of background. Uses the Nonfi
 ction Core Application led by the IDA and Sundance Institute. PROJECT ELIG
 IBILITY: feature-length documentary films (45 minutes or longer\; experime
 ntal nonfiction accepted) or nonfiction new media projects with a film/vid
 eo component\; projects in any stage of production\; non-English projects 
 must have English subtitles and the application must be completed in Engli
 sh. INELIGIBLE: fiction projects (including narrative fiction based on a t
 rue story)\; projects where applicants are hired\, employed\, or commissio
 ned by another entity\; incomplete applications or those missing supportin
 g materials\; late submissions. APPLICANT ELIGIBILITY: 18 or older\; not c
 urrently enrolled in a degree-granting program\; individual applicants (fi
 scal sponsors permitted)\; applicant must be the director or producer of t
 he project. SELECTION CRITERIA: strength of proposal and artistic approach
 \; feasibility\; ethics and accountability\; completeness\; and meeting el
 igibility requirements. ACCESSIBILITY: alternative application methods ava
 ilable (email filmfund@axslab.org by 24 July 2026)\; an Application Assist
 ance Stipend is offered for 2026 to allow applicants to hire an applicatio
 n assistant\, available first-come\, first-served (not guaranteed). TIMELI
 NE: open call opens 1 June 2026 (12:00 AM EST)\; deadline 31 July 2026 (11
 :59 PM EST). Apply via SurveyMonkey Apply.\n\nOrganisation: AXS Film Fund\
 nLocation: Remote (worldwide\; English-language application\; non-English 
 projects must have English subtitles)\nAward: Up to $10\,000 per grant\; u
 p to 5 creators awarded (aim to support 3-5 artists in this round). Applic
 ation Assistance Stipends also available on a first-come\, first-served ba
 sis to hire an application assistant. No application fee.\nDuration: Proje
 ct-based (any stage of production: pre-production\, production\, post-prod
 uction\, or distribution)\n\nMore: https://axsfilmfundapply.smapply.us/pro
 g/axs_film_fund_open_call_2026/
URL:https://axsfilmfundapply.smapply.us/prog/axs_film_fund_open_call_2026/
LOCATION:Remote (worldwide\; English-language application\; non-English pro
 jects must have English subtitles)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:small-file-media-festival-2026-call-for-work@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260620T074418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260701
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260702
SUMMARY:Deadline: Small File Media Festival 2026 - Call for Work
DESCRIPTION:The Small File Media Festival 2026 invites moving-image submiss
 ions under the theme "Can Small Files Save the World?" -- a call for artho
 use\, video work\, glitch aesthetics\, punk\, sci-fi\, narrative\, and doc
 umentary work made with a small-file mindset. This year the festival espec
 ially welcomes small-scale experiments with narrative and documentary. The
  festival frames Small File Ecomedia as a political and ecological interve
 ntion: small files function in regions with precarious infrastructure\, ci
 rcumvent bandwidth imperialism and surveillance\, and expose the environme
 ntal cost of mainstream online video. WHAT THEY WANT: craftily composed\, 
 elegantly performed\, and artfully minimised movies in any genre\; use of 
 obsolete technologies\, creative compression techniques\, and low-bandwidt
 h aesthetics at all stages of production is encouraged. Resources for maki
 ng small-file work at www.smallfile.ca/make. Open to artists\, activists\,
  media pirates\, rogue technologists\, and filmmakers. No payment or submi
 ssion fee stated. All submitted information used for festival programming 
 and promotion -- ensure accurate spelling\, punctuation\, and capitalisati
 on. Submissions close 1 July 2026 at midnight. Submit at https://smallfile
 .ca/submit/.\n\nOrganisation: Small File Media Society\nLocation: Canada\;
  festival screening. Open to international submissions.\nAward: No payment
  stated\; festival programming and screening. No submission fee stated.\nD
 uration: One-time festival screening.\n\nMore: https://smallfile.ca/submit
 /
URL:https://smallfile.ca/submit/
LOCATION:Canada\; festival screening. Open to international submissions.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:future-vision-xprize-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260620T074418Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260925
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260926
SUMMARY:Deadline: Future Vision XPRIZE (sci-fi film competition)
DESCRIPTION:Future Vision XPRIZE is a sci-fi film competition challenging f
 ilmmakers to portray an optimistic\, abundant future for humanity rather t
 han a dystopian one. CHALLENGE: create a 3-minute sci-fi trailer that depi
 cts a bold\, original\, hopeful vision of progress. PRIZES: USD 3.5 millio
 n-plus total\; the grand prize winner gets USD 2.6 million-plus to turn th
 eir trailer into a feature film\, plus over USD 1 million in prizes for ru
 nners-up. BACKGROUND: launched by the nonprofit XPRIZE and funded by Peter
  Diamandis\, with Google and Range as partners\; inspired by the optimism 
 of Star Trek and intended to give storytellers a hopeful 'north star' for 
 builders. TIMELINE: competition launched 9 March 2026\; finals on 25 Septe
 mber 2026 in Los Angeles (finalists attend in person). APPLY: register and
  read the rules on the contest website. NOTE: confirm the exact submission
  deadline\, eligibility\, and team rules on futurevisionxprize.com\; the 2
 5 September 2026 date listed here is the finals event date.\n\nOrganisatio
 n: XPRIZE (Future Vision XPRIZE\, funded by Peter Diamandis\; partners Goo
 gle and Range)\nLocation: Online / Worldwide (finals held in Los Angeles)\
 nAward: USD 3.5 million-plus prize pool. Grand prize winner receives USD 2
 .6 million-plus to develop their vision into a feature film\, with over US
 D 1 million in additional prizes for runners-up.\nDuration: One-off compet
 ition\; create a 3-minute sci-fi trailer\n\nMore: https://futurevisionxpri
 ze.com/
URL:https://futurevisionxprize.com/
LOCATION:Online / Worldwide (finals held in Los Angeles)
END:VEVENT
